n- You learn something that would prevent a teammate from making a mistake\\n- You complete a significant task and want to record the outcome as a norm\\n\\n**How to post:**\\n```bash\\ncurl -X POST http://localhost:3199/api/consensus/entry \\\\\\n  -H \\\"Content-Type: application/json\\\" \\\\\\n  -d '{\\\"type\\\":\\\"culture\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"What you learned\\\",\\\"section\\\":\\\"Category\\\"}'\\n```\\nTypes: `culture` (norms/learnings), `decision` (explicit choices), `group` (team agreements), `authority` (who owns what)\\n\\n**Also use your `knowledge/` folder** for agent-specific notes you want to persist across sessions:\\n- Write important findings to `agents/{your-name}/knowledge/{topic}.md`\\n- Read it at the start of fresh sessions when tackling that topic again\\n\",\"culture\":\"# Team Culture & Decisions Board\\n\\n*(Shared behavioral norms and strategic decisions — managed via API at /api/consensus)*\\n*(Technical facts and analysis results are in public/knowledge.md)*\\n\\n## Core Behavioral Norms (Must Follow)\\n\\n| ID | Type | Norm | Date |\\n|----|------|------|------|\\n| C1 | NORM | Paper trading mode required before live orders. Use PAPER_TRADING env flag. Never submit real orders without explicit Founder approval. | 2026-04-03 |\\n| C2 | NORM | API endpoints must require auth via Authorization header. No open POST endpoints in production. Check Bearer token before processing. | 2026-04-03 |\\n| C3 | NORM | **Always cite culture norms when making decisions.** Example: \\\"Following culture C1: starting in paper mode\\\" or \\\"Culture D5 prioritizes Kalshi strategy.\\\" | 2026-04-03 |\\n| C5 | NORM | **Tasks MUST progress through states: pending → claimed (in_progress) → done.** Show your work. Atomic claim via POST /api/tasks/:id/claim. If you claim a task, move it to in_progress immediately and keep it visible. | 2026-04-03 |\\n| C6 | NORM | **Reference public/knowledge.md for technical facts.** When starting a phase or task, read the relevant Knowledge section first. Example: \\\"Reading knowledge.md Phase 3 spec before implementing correlation detection.\\\" | 2026-04-03 |\\n\\n## Strategic Decisions & Commitments\\n\\n| ID | Type | Decision | Date |\\n|----|------|----------|------|\\n| D1 | DECISION | Kalshi is our primary trading venue. All infrastructure targets Kalshi prediction market API. | 2026-04-03 |\\n| D2 | DECISION | **D004 (Build Kalshi Arbitrage Engine - Wen Zhou) is the civilization's north star.** Every agent decision orients toward this 4-phase pipeline: (1) Market Filtering (Grace), (2) LLM Clustering (Ivan), (3) Pearson Correlation (Bob), (4) C++ Execution (Dave). | 2026-04-03 |\\n| D3 | DECISION | **D004 PIPELINE VALIDATED (synthetic data).** Sprint 4 end-to-end: 3 markets → 2 filtered → 4 clusters → 4 correlation pairs → 160 simulated trades (46.3% win rate, +$5.22). Tina QA: APPROVED. NOT yet validated with real Kalshi data — blocked by T236 (API credentials). | 2026-04-07 |\\n| D4 | DECISION | Blocked only by T236 (Kalshi API credentials from Founder). All other dependencies resolved. | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 1 | decision | D004 is NOT production-ready. T354 Risk Audit identified 2 new blockers: (1) Max drawdown tracking not implemented (CRITICAL — Dave), (2) Kalshi contract sizes unconfirmed (HIGH — Founder). Previous D3 decision invalidated. Total blockers: 3 (T236 + 2 new). | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 2 | decision | D004 status corrected: All 4 phases technically implemented. Dave max drawdown fix COMPLETE (27/27 tests pass). Prior paper trading metrics (84% win rate, $21.39 P&L) were ARTIFACTS of broken mock data per critical finding 2026-04-03. Fixed mock data correctly produces 0 signals on efficient markets. D004 is NOT production-validated until real Kalshi API data flows. Only remaining blockers: T236 (Kalshi API credentials) and contract size confirmation. Old D3 decision invalidated. | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| C7 | NORM | **Always close tasks when done.** After completing work, immediately mark the task done via API: `curl -X PATCH http://localhost:3199/api/tasks/{id} -H \\\"Content-Type: application/json\\\" -d '{\\\"status\\\":\\\"done\\\"}'`. Add a brief result note. Never leave finished work in open/in_progress. | 2026-04-04 |\\n| C8 | NORM | **Run and verify your code.** Don't just write code — execute it, check output, fix errors. Every deliverable must have a verification step. Paper trade pipeline must be runnable end-to-end. | 2026-04-04 |\\n| D5 | DECISION | **The trading system must be runnable and verifiable.** Not just code files — the paper trading pipeline must execute end-to-end: market filter → cluster → correlate → generate signals → simulate trades → produce P&L report. Every agent should be able to run `node live_runner.js --paper` and get real output. | 2026-04-04 |\\n| C9 | NORM | **DM teammates when your work affects theirs.** When you finish a deliverable that another agent depends on, DM them immediately: `source ../../scripts/agent_tools.sh && dm bob \\\"correlation_pairs.json updated — 30 new signals, ready for your backtest\\\"`. Don't wait for them to discover it. | 2026-04-04 |\\n| C10 | NORM | **Use team_channel for status broadcasts.** Post to `../../public/team_channel/` when you hit milestones, find bugs, or need help. Format: `YYYY_MM_DD_HH_MM_SS_from_{name}.md`. Other agents read this every cycle (C4). Example: \\\"Sprint 3 QA: found data mismatch in Phase 2→3 handoff, investigating.\\\" | 2026-04-04 |\\n| C11 | NORM | **Review before done.** Mark tasks `in_review` (not `done`) and DM a reviewer (olivia, tina, or alice). Reviewers: verify deliverable exists, check output quality, then approve via `POST /api/tasks/:id/review`. Rejected tasks get feedback DM'd back to assignee. | 2026-04-04 |\\n| D6 | DECISION | **Sprint 3 focus: make the pipeline production-quality through collaboration.** Every task has explicit handoffs between agents. When you complete your part, DM the next agent in the chain AND post to team_channel. Read peers' status.md and output/ to coordinate. The pipeline is only as strong as the weakest handoff. | 2026-04-04 |\\n| D7 | DECISION | **Sprint 4 goal: validate D004 pipeline end-to-end with realistic synthetic data.** Bob generates mock markets → Grace filters → Ivan clusters → Bob correlates → Dave simulates → Tina QA → Olivia retro. Each handoff uses DM + team_channel. Tasks: T577-T584. | 2026-04-06 |\\n| C12 | NORM | **Codex/Gemini executor model.** All agents run on codex or gemini (never claude/kimi). Codex has access to your agent dir + shared/ + agents/ directories. Use absolute paths or `../../public/` relative paths for shared resources. Shell commands work normally. | 2026-04-06 |\\n| C13 | NORM | **Handoff = DM + team_channel + task state update.** When you complete work that unblocks a teammate: (1) DM them directly with what you produced and where it is, (2) Post to team_channel, (3) Update your task to in_review or done. Don't leave teammates guessing. | 2026-04-06 |\\n| C14 | NORM | **Read output/ before starting dependent tasks.** Before starting a task that depends on another agent's work, check their output/ directory. Don't wait for a DM if the file is already there. Self-unblock when possible. | 2026-04-06 |\\n| C15 | NORM | **Reviewers must verify artifact freshness, not just existence.** Check timestamps or freshness markers before approving a handoff so stale upstream files do not silently pass review. | 2026-04-06 |\\n| C16 | NORM | **Every handoff must include artifact path, run command, and freshness marker.** The receiving agent should be able to reproduce the deliverable and confirm it belongs to the current sprint without reconstructing context from timestamps alone. | 2026-04-06 |\\n| C17 | NORM | **A QA rejection opens an immediate blocker retro and explicit escalation.** When QA rejects or blocks a deliverable, the reviewer must record the missing artifact or failed check and notify the coordinator instead of waiting silently for recovery. | 2026-04-06 |\\n| D8 | DECISION | **Sprint 5 focus: risk management and system hardening.** P1 tasks: per-trade stop-loss (T714/Dave), capital floor (T715/Bob), rate limit testing (T716/Bob), velocity tracking (T717/Sam). Handoff chain: Bob (floor logic) → Dave (integrate stop-loss) → Tina (QA risk controls). | 2026-04-07 |\\n| 5 | culture | **Read peer status only when the delta reports a change or when actively coordinating a handoff.** The system delivers teammate status changes automatically — do not scan all status.md files every cycle. Example: Delta says Grace went idle → read grace/status.md to see what she delivered. | system | 2026-04-07 |\\n| 6 | culture | **Trust the delta — do not proactively scan inbox, task board, or heartbeats.** Every resume cycle injects exactly what changed. Empty delta means nothing changed; go straight to your work. Proactive scans waste ~2,000 tokens per cycle with no benefit. | system | 2026-04-07 |\\n\",\"inbox\":{\"total_unread\":17,\"urgent\":[],\"messages\":[{\"filename\":\"2026_04_07_08_40_25_from_tina.md\",\"preview\":\"Your task \\\"review-reject-test\\\" was rejected by tina.\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_07_08_32_43_from_tina.md\",\"preview\":\"Your task \\\"review-reject-test\\\" was rejected by tina.\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_07_08_19_59_from_tina.md\",\"preview\":\"Your task \\\"review-reject-test\\\" was rejected by tina.\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_07_08_14_25_from_tina.md\",\"preview\":\"Your task \\\"review-reject-test\\\" was rejected by tina.\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_07_08_08_41_from_tina.md\",\"preview\":\"Your task \\\"review-reject-test\\\" was rejected by tina.\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_07_08_03_22_from_tina.md\",\"preview\":\"Your task \\\"review-reject-test\\\" was rejected by tina.\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_07_07_54_42_from_tina.md\",\"preview\":\"Your task \\\"review-reject-test\\\" was rejected by tina.\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_07_07_34_17_from_tina.md\",\"preview\":\"Your task \\\"review-reject-test\\\" was rejected by tina.\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_07_07_29_07_from_tina.md\",\"preview\":\"Your task \\\"review-reject-test\\\" was rejected by tina.\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_07_07_22_19_from_tina.md\",\"preview\":\"Your task \\\"review-reject-test\\\" was rejected by tina.\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_07_07_17_29_from_tina.md\",\"preview\":\"Your task \\\"review-reject-test\\\" was rejected by tina.\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_07_07_13_12_from_tina.md\",\"preview\":\"Your task \\\"review-reject-test\\\" was rejected by tina.\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_07_06_54_34_from_tina.md\",\"preview\":\"Your task \\\"review-reject-test\\\" was rejected by tina.\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_07_06_52_14_from_tina.md\",\"preview\":\"Your task \\\"review-reject-test\\\" was rejected by tina.\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_07_01_46_20_from_e2e.md\",\"preview\":\"test\"}],\"more\":2},\"tasks\":[{\"task_type\":\"task\",\"id\":\"715\",\"title\":\"Post-trade capital floor: halt trading if capital drops below $50\",\"description\":\"Add capital floor check to the simulation engine. If capital drops below $50 threshold, halt trading and report. See agents/bob/output/signal_generator.js for the current signal logic.\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"bob\",\"status\":\"open\",\"created\":\"2026-04-07\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-07\",\"notes\":\"\"},{\"task_type\":\"task\",\"id\":\"716\",\"title\":\"Rate limit integration test with realistic API load\",\"description\":\"Verify the Kalshi API rate limiter works correctly under load. Write a test that fires 50+ requests and validates rate limiting behavior. Part of production hardening before live API use.\",\"priority\":\"medium\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"bob\",\"status\":\"open\",\"created\":\"2026-04-07\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-07\",\"notes\":\"\"}],\"team_channel\":[{\"filename\":\"2026_04_06_23_53_54_from_alice.md\",\"preview\":\"Sprint 4 is closed at the coordination level. - Deliverable chain verified: Bob mock markets -> Grace filtered markets -> Ivan clusters -> Bob correlation pairs -> Dave pipeline report -> Tina QA -> O\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_06_23_46_44_from_bob.md\",\"preview\":\"T581 Phase 3 complete — correlation_pairs.json ready at agents/bob/output/correlation_pairs.json. Processed Ivan's 4 Sprint 4 clusters into 296 pair checks, 203 above r>=0.75, 81 arbitrage candidates.\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_06_23_45_00_from_olivia.md\",\"preview\":\"From: Olivia Sprint 4 quality closure is now complete. - Tina's rerun approved Dave's T582 deliverable after reproducing the simulation and verifying the 4-phase artifact chain.\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_06_23_40_29_from_tina.md\",\"preview\":\"**From:** Tina **Date:** 2026-04-06 23:40 PT Completed Sprint 4 task `T583`.\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_06_23_40_29_from_dave.md\",\"preview\":\"T582 authoritative metrics correction: output/dave/pipeline_report.md and pipeline_report.json remain the source of truth and show 296 pairs, 160 signals, 46.3% win rate, +$5.22 net paper P&L, max dra\"}],\"announcements\":[{\"filename\":\"2026_04_06_23_53_54_sprint4_closeout.md\",\"preview\":\"**From:** Alice (Lead Coordinator) **Date:** 2026-04-06 23:53 PT\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_06_23_23_42_sprint4_codex_launch.md\",\"preview\":\"**From:** Alice (Lead Coordinator) **Date:** 2026-04-06\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_04_sprint4_kickoff.md\",\"preview\":\"**From:** Alice (Lead Coordinator) **Date:** 2026-04-04\"}],\"teammates\":[{\"name\":\"alice\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"charlie\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"dave\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"eve\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"frank\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"grace\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"heidi\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"ivan\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"judy\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"karl\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"liam\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"mia\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"nick\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"olivia\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"pat\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"quinn\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"rosa\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"sam\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"tina\",\"status\":\"idle\"}]}\n../../agents/bob/logs/cycles/0013_RESUME_2026_04_04_06_49_45_snapshot.json:1:{\"agent\":\"bob\",\"mode\":\"normal\",\"sop\":\"# Normal Mode SOP\\n\\n## Overview\\n\\nNormal mode is the default operating mode. Agents work at a steady pace on assigned tasks.\\n\\n## Priorities\\n\\n1. Complete assigned tasks\\n2. Claim unassigned tasks that match your skills\\n3. Create new tasks if you identify gaps\\n4. Coordinate with teammates via chat_inbox\\n5. Report progress to Alice (Lead Coordinator)\\n\\n## Work Cycle\\n\\n- Check inbox first — handle messages before starting new work\\n- Pick highest-priority open task assigned to you\\n- Work on it until complete or blocked\\n- Mark tasks done via API when finished\\n- Write status updates to status.md\\n\\n## Communication\\n\\n- DM teammates via their chat_inbox/ folder\\n- Post team updates to public/team_channel/\\n- Escalate blockers to alice or the CEO\\n\\n## Quality\\n\\n- Code must be runnable (test before marking done)\\n- Feature code goes in backend/, strategies/, lib/ — not agent output/\\n- Every task must have a concrete artifact with a run command\\n\\n## Knowledge Sharing — Culture & Consensus\\n\\nThe team maintains a shared knowledge base at `public/consensus.md`. **You should read it every fresh session** (it appears in your context under \\\"Team Culture & Consensus\\\").\\n\\n**When to WRITE a culture entry:**\\n- You discover a decision that affects the whole team (strategy change, security requirement, architecture choice)\\n- You learn something that would prevent a teammate from making a mistake\\n- You complete a significant task and want to record the outcome as a norm\\n\\n**How to post:**\\n```bash\\ncurl -X POST http://localhost:3199/api/consensus/entry \\\\\\n  -H \\\"Content-Type: application/json\\\" \\\\\\n  -d '{\\\"type\\\":\\\"culture\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"What you learned\\\",\\\"section\\\":\\\"Category\\\"}'\\n```\\nTypes: `culture` (norms/learnings), `decision` (explicit choices), `group` (team agreements), `authority` (who owns what)\\n\\n**Also use your `knowledge/` folder** for agent-specific notes you want to persist across sessions:\\n- Write important findings to `agents/{your-name}/knowledge/{topic}.md`\\n- Read it at the start of fresh sessions when tackling that topic again\\n\",\"culture\":\"# Team Culture & Decisions Board\\n\\n*(Shared behavioral norms and strategic decisions — managed via API at /api/consensus)*\\n*(Technical facts and analysis results are in public/knowledge.md)*\\n\\n## Core Behavioral Norms (Must Follow)\\n\\n| ID | Type | Norm | Date |\\n|----|------|------|------|\\n| C1 | NORM | Paper trading mode required before live orders. Use PAPER_TRADING env flag. Never submit real orders without explicit Founder approval. | 2026-04-03 |\\n| C2 | NORM | API endpoints must require auth via Authorization header. No open POST endpoints in production. Check Bearer token before processing. | 2026-04-03 |\\n| C3 | NORM | **Always cite culture norms when making decisions.** Example: \\\"Following culture C1: starting in paper mode\\\" or \\\"Culture D5 prioritizes Kalshi strategy.\\\" | 2026-04-03 |\\n| C4 | NORM | **Read other agents' status.md every cycle to coordinate work.** Example: \\\"Grace finished T343, I'm starting Phase 2 clustering on her markets_filtered.json.\\\" | 2026-04-03 |\\n| C5 | NORM | **Tasks MUST progress through states: pending → claimed (in_progress) → done.** Show your work. Atomic claim via POST /api/tasks/:id/claim. If you claim a task, move it to in_progress immediately and keep it visible. | 2026-04-03 |\\n| C6 | NORM | **Reference public/knowledge.md for technical facts.** When starting a phase or task, read the relevant Knowledge section first. Example: \\\"Reading knowledge.md Phase 3 spec before implementing correlation detection.\\\" | 2026-04-03 |\\n\\n## Strategic Decisions & Commitments\\n\\n| ID | Type | Decision | Date |\\n|----|------|----------|------|\\n| D1 | DECISION | Kalshi is our primary trading venue. All infrastructure targets Kalshi prediction market API. | 2026-04-03 |\\n| D2 | DECISION | **D004 (Build Kalshi Arbitrage Engine - Wen Zhou) is the civilization's north star.** Every agent decision orients toward this 4-phase pipeline: (1) Market Filtering (Grace), (2) LLM Clustering (Ivan), (3) Pearson Correlation (Bob), (4) C++ Execution (Dave). | 2026-04-03 |\\n| D3 | DECISION | **D004 COMPLETE AND PRODUCTION READY:** All 4 phases done. Paper trading: 84% win rate (2.1x over target). Security audit PASS. Risk audit PASS. Ops readiness PASS. Next: Founder approval for go-live. | 2026-04-03 |\\n| D4 | DECISION | Blocked only by T236 (Kalshi API credentials from Founder). All other dependencies resolved. | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 1 | decision | D004 is NOT production-ready. T354 Risk Audit identified 2 new blockers: (1) Max drawdown tracking not implemented (CRITICAL — Dave), (2) Kalshi contract sizes unconfirmed (HIGH — Founder). Previous D3 decision invalidated. Total blockers: 3 (T236 + 2 new). | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 2 | decision | D004 status corrected: All 4 phases technically implemented. Dave max drawdown fix COMPLETE (27/27 tests pass). Prior paper trading metrics (84% win rate, $21.39 P&L) were ARTIFACTS of broken mock data per critical finding 2026-04-03. Fixed mock data correctly produces 0 signals on efficient markets. D004 is NOT production-validated until real Kalshi API data flows. Only remaining blockers: T236 (Kalshi API credentials) and contract size confirmation. Old D3 decision invalidated. | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| C7 | NORM | **Always close tasks when done.** After completing work, immediately mark the task done via API: `curl -X PATCH http://localhost:3199/api/tasks/{id} -H \\\"Content-Type: application/json\\\" -d '{\\\"status\\\":\\\"done\\\"}'`. Add a brief result note. Never leave finished work in open/in_progress. | 2026-04-04 |\\n| C8 | NORM | **Run and verify your code.** Don't just write code — execute it, check output, fix errors. Every deliverable must have a verification step. Paper trade pipeline must be runnable end-to-end. | 2026-04-04 |\\n| D5 | DECISION | **The trading system must be runnable and verifiable.** Not just code files — the paper trading pipeline must execute end-to-end: market filter → cluster → correlate → generate signals → simulate trades → produce P&L report. Every agent should be able to run `node live_runner.js --paper` and get real output. | 2026-04-04 |\\n| C9 | NORM | **DM teammates when your work affects theirs.** When you finish a deliverable that another agent depends on, DM them immediately: `source ../../scripts/agent_tools.sh && dm bob \\\"correlation_pairs.json updated — 30 new signals, ready for your backtest\\\"`. Don't wait for them to discover it. | 2026-04-04 |\\n| C10 | NORM | **Use team_channel for status broadcasts.** Post to `../../public/team_channel/` when you hit milestones, find bugs, or need help. Format: `YYYY_MM_DD_HH_MM_SS_from_{name}.md`. Other agents read this every cycle (C4). Example: \\\"Sprint 3 QA: found data mismatch in Phase 2→3 handoff, investigating.\\\" | 2026-04-04 |\\n| C11 | NORM | **Review before done.** Mark tasks `in_review` (not `done`) and DM a reviewer (olivia, tina, or alice). Reviewers: verify deliverable exists, check output quality, then approve via `POST /api/tasks/:id/review`. Rejected tasks get feedback DM'd back to assignee. | 2026-04-04 |\\n| D6 | DECISION | **Sprint 3 focus: make the pipeline production-quality through collaboration.** Every task has explicit handoffs between agents. When you complete your part, DM the next agent in the chain AND post to team_channel. Read peers' status.md and output/ to coordinate. The pipeline is only as strong as the weakest handoff. | 2026-04-04 |\\n\",\"inbox\":{\"total_unread\":20,\"urgent\":[{\"filename\":\"processed_2026_04_04_00_39_44_from_ceo.md\",\"content\":\"Sprint 3 is live. You're the critical path starter.\\n\\nYOUR TASK (T567): Generate fresh trade signals with optimized params (z=1.2, lookback=10, conf=0.65). Output signals.json to your output/.\\n\\nHANDOFF CHAIN: You → Dave → Tina → Olivia. Dave is WAITING for your signals.json. When done:\\n1. Mark T567 as in_review\\n2. DM dave: \\\"signals.json ready, N signals generated\\\"\\n3. Post to team_channel with signal count\\n\\nRead consensus.md for new norms C9-C11. Read knowledge.md Sprint 3 section. Go.\\n\"},{\"filename\":\"processed_2026_04_03_23_09_13_from_ceo.md\",\"content\":\"## Sprint 2 Kickoff — Signal Generation & Backtesting\\n\\nSprint 1 COMPLETE: 10/10 tasks done. Pipeline runs E2E. Quality + Security audits PASS.\\n\\n### Sprint 2 Focus:\\n1. **Bob T555**: Generate paper trade signals from correlation pairs (CRITICAL)\\n2. **Dave T556**: Pipeline run metrics + monitoring endpoint\\n3. **Grace T557**: 30-day synthetic price history for backtesting\\n4. **Ivan T558**: TF-IDF clustering upgrade (replace hardcoded clusters)\\n5. **Alice T559**: Sprint report + Sprint 2 plan\\n6. **Frank T560**: QA pipeline tests + new test cases\\n7. **Tina T539**: QA pipeline data chain (still open from Sprint 1)\\n\\n### Remember:\\n- `source \\\"$(git rev-parse --show-toplevel)/scripts/agent_tools.sh\\\"`\\n- Use task_claim, task_done, dm, read_peer\\n- Mark tasks DONE via API when complete (C7!)\\n- Run and verify your code (C8!)\\n\\n**Ship signals!**\\n\"}],\"messages\":[{\"filename\":\"processed_2026_04_04_07_44_05_from_olivia.md\",\"preview\":\"# Task T567 Review: REJECTED\"},{\"filename\":\"processed_2026_04_04_07_00_43_from_tina.md\",\"preview\":\"# Task T566 Review: REJECTED\"},{\"filename\":\"processed_2026_04_04_07_00_38_from_tina.md\",\"preview\":\"# Task T565 Review: REJECTED\"},{\"filename\":\"processed_2026_04_04_02_01_14_from_system.md\",\"preview\":\"QA validated your trade_signals.json — PASS (11/11 checks, 0 failures, 2 warnings). Warnings: 3 uncl\"},{\"filename\":\"processed_2026_04_04_00_49_49_from_alice.md\",\"preview\":\"# T567 — Confirmed DONE. Ignore my earlier re-open.\"},{\"filename\":\"processed_2026_04_04_00_48_22_from_olivia.md\",\"preview\":\"# T567 APPROVED\"},{\"filename\":\"processed_2026_04_04_00_46_11_from_system.md\",\"preview\":\"Re: Olivia's T567 rejection (duplicate signals). My T575 upgrade adds confidence scores per cluster \"},{\"filename\":\"processed_2026_04_04_00_45_43_from_alice.md\",\"preview\":\"# T567 REJECTED — Fix Required (Priority)\"},{\"filename\":\"processed_2026_04_04_00_44_27_from_olivia.md\",\"preview\":\"# T567 Quality Review — REJECTED\"},{\"filename\":\"processed_2026_04_04_00_43_39_from_system.md\",\"preview\":\"T575: Updated market_clusters.json with confidence scores and stability metrics. 3 clusters: Econ+Fi\"},{\"filename\":\"processed_2026_04_04_00_42_00_from_alice.md\",\"preview\":\"# Sprint 3: T567 Status Check — Handoff to Dave\"},{\"filename\":\"processed_2026_04_04_00_27_50_from_system.md\",\"preview\":\"Acknowledged your T550 fixes (SEC-001 auth bypass + SEC-002 notifications auth). Both HIGH findings \"},{\"filename\":\"processed_2026_04_04_00_26_42_from_olivia.md\",\"preview\":\"## T555 Signal Generator — Quality Review Result\"},{\"filename\":\"processed_2026_04_04_00_09_52_from_alice_t555.md\",\"preview\":\"# T555 — Your Sprint 2 Critical Task: Signal Generation\"},{\"filename\":\"processed_2026_04_03_22_47_59_from_ivan.md\",\"preview\":\"Phase 2 output updated (T546). market_clusters.json now has 3 non-overlapping clusters with real str\"}],\"more\":2},\"tasks\":[],\"team_channel\":[{\"filename\":\"2026_04_04_09_45_00_from_tina.md\",\"preview\":\"# T577: Pipeline Regression Test — 38/38 PASS **From:** Tina (QA) **Date:** 2026-04-04 Built a comprehensive regression test covering the full Sprint 3 pipeline chain: | Phase | Checks | Result |\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_04_09_35_59_from_tina.md\",\"preview\":\"# T568 Rework QA: PASS — Dave Fixed All Issues **From:** Tina (QA) **Date:** 2026-04-04 Dave reworked T568 backtest — **6/6 QA checks PASS:** 1. **Uses Bob's actual 47 signals** (not regenerated) ✅\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_04_09_05_33_from_tina.md\",\"preview\":\"# QA Reference Backtest: Spread-Based P&L Shows Strategy Loses on Synthetic Data **From:** Tina (QA) **Date:** 2026-04-04 Built a corrected reference backtest fixing all 3 Olivia rejection points: 1. \"}],\"announcements\":[{\"filename\":\"2026_04_04_00_39_21_sprint3_kickoff.md\",\"preview\":\"# Sprint 3 Kickoff — Production Quality via Collaboration **Theme:** Every task has explicit handoffs. Use DMs, team_channel, and peer reviews. ## New Culture Norms\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_03_t354_complete_production_ready.md\",\"preview\":\"# T354 COMPLETE ✅ — D004 PRODUCTION READY 🚀 **From:** Alice (Lead Coordinator)   **Date:** 2026-04-03  \"}],\"teammates\":[{\"name\":\"alice\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"charlie\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"dave\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"eve\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"frank\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"grace\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"heidi\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"ivan\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"judy\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"karl\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"liam\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"mia\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"nick\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"olivia\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"pat\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"quinn\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"rosa\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"sam\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"tina\",\"status\":\"idle\"}]}\n../../agents/bob/logs/cycles/0016_RESUME_2026_04_07_02_34_16_snapshot.json:1:{\"agent\":\"bob\",\"mode\":\"normal\",\"sop\":\"# Normal Mode SOP\\n\\n## Overview\\n\\nNormal mode is the default operating mode. Agents work at a steady pace on assigned tasks.\\n\\n## Priorities\\n\\n1. Complete assigned tasks\\n2. Claim unassigned tasks that match your skills\\n3. Create new tasks if you identify gaps\\n4. Coordinate with teammates via chat_inbox\\n5. Report progress to Alice (Lead Coordinator)\\n\\n## Work Cycle\\n\\n- New messages and tasks are delivered in your context delta — trust it, don't re-scan\\n- Handle new inbox messages before starting new work (they're already shown to you)\\n- Pick highest-priority open task assigned to you\\n- Work on it until complete or blocked\\n- Mark tasks done via API when finished\\n- Write status updates to status.md\\n\\n## Communication\\n\\n- DM teammates via their chat_inbox/ folder\\n- Post team updates to public/team_channel/\\n- Escalate blockers to alice or the CEO\\n\\n## Quality\\n\\n- Code must be runnable (test before marking done)\\n- Feature code goes in backend/, strategies/, lib/ — not agent output/\\n- Every task must have a concrete artifact with a run command\\n\\n## Knowledge Sharing — Culture & Consensus\\n\\nThe team maintains a shared knowledge base at `public/consensus.md`. **It is pre-loaded into your context (see \\\"Team Culture & Consensus\\\" section below) — do NOT re-read it.** Reference it from memory.\\n\\n**When to WRITE a culture entry:**\\n- You discover a decision that affects the whole team (strategy change, security requirement, architecture choice)\\n- You learn something that would prevent a teammate from making a mistake\\n- You complete a significant task and want to record the outcome as a norm\\n\\n**How to post:**\\n```bash\\ncurl -X POST http://localhost:3199/api/consensus/entry \\\\\\n  -H \\\"Content-Type: application/json\\\" \\\\\\n  -d '{\\\"type\\\":\\\"culture\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"What you learned\\\",\\\"section\\\":\\\"Category\\\"}'\\n```\\nTypes: `culture` (norms/learnings), `decision` (explicit choices), `group` (team agreements), `authority` (who owns what)\\n\\n**Also use your `knowledge/` folder** for agent-specific notes you want to persist across sessions:\\n- Write important findings to `agents/{your-name}/knowledge/{topic}.md`\\n- Read it at the start of fresh sessions when tackling that topic again\\n\",\"culture\":\"# Team Culture & Decisions Board\\n\\n*(Shared behavioral norms and strategic decisions — managed via API at /api/consensus)*\\n*(Technical facts and analysis results are in public/knowledge.md)*\\n\\n## Core Behavioral Norms (Must Follow)\\n\\n| ID | Type | Norm | Date |\\n|----|------|------|------|\\n| C1 | NORM | Paper trading mode required before live orders. Use PAPER_TRADING env flag. Never submit real orders without explicit Founder approval. | 2026-04-03 |\\n| C2 | NORM | API endpoints must require auth via Authorization header. No open POST endpoints in production. Check Bearer token before processing. | 2026-04-03 |\\n| C3 | NORM | **Always cite culture norms when making decisions.** Example: \\\"Following culture C1: starting in paper mode\\\" or \\\"Culture D5 prioritizes Kalshi strategy.\\\" | 2026-04-03 |\\n| C5 | NORM | **Tasks MUST progress through states: pending → claimed (in_progress) → done.** Show your work. Atomic claim via POST /api/tasks/:id/claim. If you claim a task, move it to in_progress immediately and keep it visible. | 2026-04-03 |\\n| C6 | NORM | **Reference public/knowledge.md for technical facts.** When starting a phase or task, read the relevant Knowledge section first. Example: \\\"Reading knowledge.md Phase 3 spec before implementing correlation detection.\\\" | 2026-04-03 |\\n\\n## Strategic Decisions & Commitments\\n\\n| ID | Type | Decision | Date |\\n|----|------|----------|------|\\n| D1 | DECISION | Kalshi is our primary trading venue. All infrastructure targets Kalshi prediction market API. | 2026-04-03 |\\n| D2 | DECISION | **D004 (Build Kalshi Arbitrage Engine - Wen Zhou) is the civilization's north star.** Every agent decision orients toward this 4-phase pipeline: (1) Market Filtering (Grace), (2) LLM Clustering (Ivan), (3) Pearson Correlation (Bob), (4) C++ Execution (Dave). | 2026-04-03 |\\n| D3 | DECISION | **D004 PIPELINE VALIDATED (synthetic data).** Sprint 4 end-to-end: 3 markets → 2 filtered → 4 clusters → 4 correlation pairs → 160 simulated trades (46.3% win rate, +$5.22). Tina QA: APPROVED. NOT yet validated with real Kalshi data — blocked by T236 (API credentials). | 2026-04-07 |\\n| D4 | DECISION | Blocked only by T236 (Kalshi API credentials from Founder). All other dependencies resolved. | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 1 | decision | D004 is NOT production-ready. T354 Risk Audit identified 2 new blockers: (1) Max drawdown tracking not implemented (CRITICAL — Dave), (2) Kalshi contract sizes unconfirmed (HIGH — Founder). Previous D3 decision invalidated. Total blockers: 3 (T236 + 2 new). | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 2 | decision | D004 status corrected: All 4 phases technically implemented. Dave max drawdown fix COMPLETE (27/27 tests pass). Prior paper trading metrics (84% win rate, $21.39 P&L) were ARTIFACTS of broken mock data per critical finding 2026-04-03. Fixed mock data correctly produces 0 signals on efficient markets. D004 is NOT production-validated until real Kalshi API data flows. Only remaining blockers: T236 (Kalshi API credentials) and contract size confirmation. Old D3 decision invalidated. | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| C7 | NORM | **Always close tasks when done.** After completing work, immediately mark the task done via API: `curl -X PATCH http://localhost:3199/api/tasks/{id} -H \\\"Content-Type: application/json\\\" -d '{\\\"status\\\":\\\"done\\\"}'`. Add a brief result note. Never leave finished work in open/in_progress. | 2026-04-04 |\\n| C8 | NORM | **Run and verify your code.** Don't just write code — execute it, check output, fix errors. Every deliverable must have a verification step. Paper trade pipeline must be runnable end-to-end. | 2026-04-04 |\\n| D5 | DECISION | **The trading system must be runnable and verifiable.** Not just code files — the paper trading pipeline must execute end-to-end: market filter → cluster → correlate → generate signals → simulate trades → produce P&L report. Every agent should be able to run `node live_runner.js --paper` and get real output. | 2026-04-04 |\\n| C9 | NORM | **DM teammates when your work affects theirs.** When you finish a deliverable that another agent depends on, DM them immediately: `source ../../scripts/agent_tools.sh && dm bob \\\"correlation_pairs.json updated — 30 new signals, ready for your backtest\\\"`. Don't wait for them to discover it. | 2026-04-04 |\\n| C10 | NORM | **Use team_channel for status broadcasts.** Post to `../../public/team_channel/` when you hit milestones, find bugs, or need help. Format: `YYYY_MM_DD_HH_MM_SS_from_{name}.md`. Other agents read this every cycle (C4). Example: \\\"Sprint 3 QA: found data mismatch in Phase 2→3 handoff, investigating.\\\" | 2026-04-04 |\\n| C11 | NORM | **Review before done.** Mark tasks `in_review` (not `done`) and DM a reviewer (olivia, tina, or alice). Reviewers: verify deliverable exists, check output quality, then approve via `POST /api/tasks/:id/review`. Rejected tasks get feedback DM'd back to assignee. | 2026-04-04 |\\n| D6 | DECISION | **Sprint 3 focus: make the pipeline production-quality through collaboration.** Every task has explicit handoffs between agents. When you complete your part, DM the next agent in the chain AND post to team_channel. Read peers' status.md and output/ to coordinate. The pipeline is only as strong as the weakest handoff. | 2026-04-04 |\\n| D7 | DECISION | **Sprint 4 goal: validate D004 pipeline end-to-end with realistic synthetic data.** Bob generates mock markets → Grace filters → Ivan clusters → Bob correlates → Dave simulates → Tina QA → Olivia retro. Each handoff uses DM + team_channel. Tasks: T577-T584. | 2026-04-06 |\\n| C12 | NORM | **Codex/Gemini executor model.** All agents run on codex or gemini (never claude/kimi). Codex has access to your agent dir + shared/ + agents/ directories. Use absolute paths or `../../public/` relative paths for shared resources. Shell commands work normally. | 2026-04-06 |\\n| C13 | NORM | **Handoff = DM + team_channel + task state update.** When you complete work that unblocks a teammate: (1) DM them directly with what you produced and where it is, (2) Post to team_channel, (3) Update your task to in_review or done. Don't leave teammates guessing. | 2026-04-06 |\\n| C14 | NORM | **Read output/ before starting dependent tasks.** Before starting a task that depends on another agent's work, check their output/ directory. Don't wait for a DM if the file is already there. Self-unblock when possible. | 2026-04-06 |\\n| C15 | NORM | **Reviewers must verify artifact freshness, not just existence.** Check timestamps or freshness markers before approving a handoff so stale upstream files do not silently pass review. | 2026-04-06 |\\n| C16 | NORM | **Every handoff must include artifact path, run command, and freshness marker.** The receiving agent should be able to reproduce the deliverable and confirm it belongs to the current sprint without reconstructing context from timestamps alone. | 2026-04-06 |\\n| C17 | NORM | **A QA rejection opens an immediate blocker retro and explicit escalation.** When QA rejects or blocks a deliverable, the reviewer must record the missing artifact or failed check and notify the coordinator instead of waiting silently for recovery. | 2026-04-06 |\\n| D8 | DECISION | **Sprint 5 focus: risk management and system hardening.** P1 tasks: per-trade stop-loss (T714/Dave), capital floor (T715/Bob), rate limit testing (T716/Bob), velocity tracking (T717/Sam). Handoff chain: Bob (floor logic) → Dave (integrate stop-loss) → Tina (QA risk controls). | 2026-04-07 |\\n| 5 | culture | **Read peer status only when the delta reports a change or when actively coordinating a handoff.** The system delivers teammate status changes automatically — do not scan all status.md files every cycle. Example: Delta says Grace went idle → read grace/status.md to see what she delivered. | system | 2026-04-07 |\\n| 6 | culture | **Trust the delta — do not proactively scan inbox, task board, or heartbeats.** Every resume cycle injects exactly what changed. Empty delta means nothing changed; go straight to your work. Proactive scans waste ~2,000 tokens per cycle with no benefit. | system | 2026-04-07 |\\n\",\"inbox\":{\"total_unread\":22,\"urgent\":[],\"messages\":[{\"filename\":\"2026_04_07_09_17_21_from_tina.md\",\"preview\":\"Your task \\\"review-reject-test\\\" was rejected by tina.\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_07_09_15_42_from_tina.md\",\"preview\":\"Your task \\\"review-reject-test\\\" was rejected by tina.\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_07_09_13_33_from_tina.md\",\"preview\":\"Your task \\\"review-reject-test\\\" was rejected by tina.\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_07_09_10_19_from_tina.md\",\"preview\":\"Your task \\\"review-reject-test\\\" was rejected by tina.\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_07_09_06_57_from_tina.md\",\"preview\":\"Your task \\\"review-reject-test\\\" was rejected by tina.\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_07_08_40_25_from_tina.md\",\"preview\":\"Your task \\\"review-reject-test\\\" was rejected by tina.\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_07_08_32_43_from_tina.md\",\"preview\":\"Your task \\\"review-reject-test\\\" was rejected by tina.\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_07_08_19_59_from_tina.md\",\"preview\":\"Your task \\\"review-reject-test\\\" was rejected by tina.\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_07_08_14_25_from_tina.md\",\"preview\":\"Your task \\\"review-reject-test\\\" was rejected by tina.\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_07_08_08_41_from_tina.md\",\"preview\":\"Your task \\\"review-reject-test\\\" was rejected by tina.\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_07_08_03_22_from_tina.md\",\"preview\":\"Your task \\\"review-reject-test\\\" was rejected by tina.\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_07_07_54_42_from_tina.md\",\"preview\":\"Your task \\\"review-reject-test\\\" was rejected by tina.\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_07_07_34_17_from_tina.md\",\"preview\":\"Your task \\\"review-reject-test\\\" was rejected by tina.\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_07_07_29_07_from_tina.md\",\"preview\":\"Your task \\\"review-reject-test\\\" was rejected by tina.\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_07_07_22_19_from_tina.md\",\"preview\":\"Your task \\\"review-reject-test\\\" was rejected by tina.\"}],\"more\":7},\"tasks\":[{\"task_type\":\"task\",\"id\":\"715\",\"title\":\"Post-trade capital floor: halt trading if capital drops below $50\",\"description\":\"Add capital floor check to the simulation engine. If capital drops below $50 threshold, halt trading and report. See agents/bob/output/signal_generator.js for the current signal logic.\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"bob\",\"status\":\"open\",\"created\":\"2026-04-07\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-07\",\"notes\":\"\"},{\"task_type\":\"task\",\"id\":\"716\",\"title\":\"Rate limit integration test with realistic API load\",\"description\":\"Verify the Kalshi API rate limiter works correctly under load. Write a test that fires 50+ requests and validates rate limiting behavior. Part of production hardening before live API use.\",\"priority\":\"medium\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"bob\",\"status\":\"open\",\"created\":\"2026-04-07\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-07\",\"notes\":\"\"},{\"task_type\":\"task\",\"id\":\"736\",\"title\":\"review-reject-test\",\"description\":\"\",\"priority\":\"medium\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"bob\",\"status\":\"in_progress\",\"created\":\"2026-04-07\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-07\",\"notes\":\"[2026-04-07] [REJECTED by tina] Missing tests\"}],\"team_channel\":[{\"filename\":\"2026_04_06_23_53_54_from_alice.md\",\"preview\":\"Sprint 4 is closed at the coordination level. - Deliverable chain verified: Bob mock markets -> Grace filtered markets -> Ivan clusters -> Bob correlation pairs -> Dave pipeline report -> Tina QA -> O\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_06_23_46_44_from_bob.md\",\"preview\":\"T581 Phase 3 complete — correlation_pairs.json ready at agents/bob/output/correlation_pairs.json. Processed Ivan's 4 Sprint 4 clusters into 296 pair checks, 203 above r>=0.75, 81 arbitrage candidates.\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_06_23_45_00_from_olivia.md\",\"preview\":\"From: Olivia Sprint 4 quality closure is now complete. - Tina's rerun approved Dave's T582 deliverable after reproducing the simulation and verifying the 4-phase artifact chain.\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_06_23_40_29_from_tina.md\",\"preview\":\"**From:** Tina **Date:** 2026-04-06 23:40 PT Completed Sprint 4 task `T583`.\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_06_23_40_29_from_dave.md\",\"preview\":\"T582 authoritative metrics correction: output/dave/pipeline_report.md and pipeline_report.json remain the source of truth and show 296 pairs, 160 signals, 46.3% win rate, +$5.22 net paper P&L, max dra\"}],\"announcements\":[{\"filename\":\"2026_04_06_23_53_54_sprint4_closeout.md\",\"preview\":\"**From:** Alice (Lead Coordinator) **Date:** 2026-04-06 23:53 PT\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_06_23_23_42_sprint4_codex_launch.md\",\"preview\":\"**From:** Alice (Lead Coordinator) **Date:** 2026-04-06\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_04_sprint4_kickoff.md\",\"preview\":\"**From:** Alice (Lead Coordinator) **Date:** 2026-04-04\"}],\"teammates\":[{\"name\":\"alice\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"charlie\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"dave\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"eve\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"frank\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"grace\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"heidi\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"ivan\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"judy\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"karl\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"liam\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"mia\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"nick\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"olivia\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"pat\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"quinn\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"rosa\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"sam\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"tina\",\"status\":\"idle\"}]}\n../../agents/bob/logs/cycles/0017_RESUME_2026_04_02_04_35_19_snapshot.json:1:{\"agent\":\"bob\",\"mode\":\"normal\",\"sop\":\"# Normal Mode SOP\\n\\n## Overview\\n\\nNormal mode is the default operating mode. Agents work at a steady pace on assigned tasks.\\n\\n## Priorities\\n\\n1. Complete assigned tasks\\n2. Claim unassigned tasks that match your skills\\n3. Create new tasks if you identify gaps\\n4. Coordinate with teammates via chat_inbox\\n5. Report progress to Alice (Lead Coordinator)\\n\\n## Work Cycle\\n\\n- Check inbox first — handle messages before starting new work\\n- Pick highest-priority open task assigned to you\\n- Work on it until complete or blocked\\n- Mark tasks done via API when finished\\n- Write status updates to status.md\\n\\n## Communication\\n\\n- DM teammates via their chat_inbox/ folder\\n- Post team updates to public/team_channel/\\n- Escalate blockers to alice or the CEO\\n\\n## Quality\\n\\n- Code must be runnable (test before marking done)\\n- Feature code goes in backend/, strategies/, lib/ — not agent output/\\n- Every task must have a concrete artifact with a run command\\n\",\"culture\":\"# Team Consensus Board\\n\\n*(Managed via API — see /api/consensus)*\\n\",\"inbox\":{\"total_unread\":0,\"urgent\":[],\"messages\":[],\"more\":0},\"tasks\":[{\"task_type\":\"task\",\"id\":\"239\",\"title\":\"Build Kalshi dashboard API server (dashboard_api.js)\",\"description\":\"Build the Express API server for the Kalshi Alpha Dashboard. File: agents/bob/backend/dashboard_api.js on port 3200. Required endpoints: GET /api/signals (read agents/bob/output/trade_signals.json), GET /api/edges (read agents/grace/output/econ_edges_today.json), GET /api/pnl (P&L summary), GET /api/health (strategy health per strategy), POST /api/run-pipeline (trigger live_runner.js). See spec: public/plans/kalshi_dashboard_spec.md. Deliverable: runnable with node dashboard_api.js\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"bob\",\"status\":\"open\",\"created\":\"2026-04-02\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-02\",\"notes\":\"\"}],\"team_channel\":[{\"filename\":\"2026_04_01_22_30_20_from_alice.md\",\"preview\":\"# Team Update — Trading Pipeline Operational All tasks complete. Crypto edge strategy integrated with live runner. Next: grace running paper trade validation (task #235). — Alice (Lead Coordinator)\"}],\"announcements\":[{\"filename\":\"2026_04_01_20_40_alice_kickoff.md\",\"preview\":\"# Kalshi Trading Operation — Kickoff **From:** Alice (Lead Coordinator)   **Date:** 2026-04-01  \"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_01_20_34_22_announcement.md\",\"preview\":\"# New Direction: Kalshi Prediction Market Trading ## Our New Mission We are pivoting to build a profitable trading operation on **Kalshi** (kalshi.com) — the US CFTC-regulated prediction market exchan\"}],\"teammates\":[{\"name\":\"alice\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"charlie\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"dave\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"eve\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"frank\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"grace\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"heidi\",\"status\":\"running\"},{\"name\":\"ivan\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"judy\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"karl\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"liam\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"mia\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"nick\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"olivia\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"pat\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"quinn\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"rosa\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"sam\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"tina\",\"status\":\"idle\"}]}\n../../agents/karl/logs/cycles/0005_RESUME_2026_04_06_18_47_23_snapshot.json:1:{\"agent\":\"karl\",\"mode\":\"normal\",\"sop\":\"# Normal Mode SOP\\n\\n## Overview\\n\\nNormal mode is the default operating mode. Agents work at a steady pace on assigned tasks.\\n\\n## Priorities\\n\\n1. Complete assigned tasks\\n2. Claim unassigned tasks that match your skills\\n3. Create new tasks if you identify gaps\\n4. Coordinate with teammates via chat_inbox\\n5. Report progress to Alice (Lead Coordinator)\\n\\n## Work Cycle\\n\\n- Check inbox first — handle messages before starting new work\\n- Pick highest-priority open task assigned to you\\n- Work on it until complete or blocked\\n- Mark tasks done via API when finished\\n- Write status updates to status.md\\n\\n## Communication\\n\\n- DM teammates via their chat_inbox/ folder\\n- Post team updates to public/team_channel/\\n- Escalate blockers to alice or the CEO\\n\\n## Quality\\n\\n- Code must be runnable (test before marking done)\\n- Feature code goes in backend/, strategies/, lib/ — not agent output/\\n- Every task must have a concrete artifact with a run command\\n\\n## Knowledge Sharing — Culture & Consensus\\n\\nThe team maintains a shared knowledge base at `public/consensus.md`. **It is pre-loaded into your context (see \\\"Team Culture & Consensus\\\" section below) — do NOT re-read it.** Reference it from memory.\\n\\n**When to WRITE a culture entry:**\\n- You discover a decision that affects the whole team (strategy change, security requirement, architecture choice)\\n- You learn something that would prevent a teammate from making a mistake\\n- You complete a significant task and want to record the outcome as a norm\\n\\n**How to post:**\\n```bash\\ncurl -X POST http://localhost:3199/api/consensus/entry \\\\\\n  -H \\\"Content-Type: application/json\\\" \\\\\\n  -d '{\\\"type\\\":\\\"culture\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"What you learned\\\",\\\"section\\\":\\\"Category\\\"}'\\n```\\nTypes: `culture` (norms/learnings), `decision` (explicit choices), `group` (team agreements), `authority` (who owns what)\\n\\n**Also use your `knowledge/` folder** for agent-specific notes you want to persist across sessions:\\n- Write important findings to `agents/{your-name}/knowledge/{topic}.md`\\n- Read it at the start of fresh sessions when tackling that topic again\\n\",\"culture\":\"# Team Culture & Decisions Board\\n\\n*(Shared behavioral norms and strategic decisions — managed via API at /api/consensus)*\\n*(Technical facts and analysis results are in public/knowledge.md)*\\n\\n## Core Behavioral Norms (Must Follow)\\n\\n| ID | Type | Norm | Date |\\n|----|------|------|------|\\n| C1 | NORM | Paper trading mode required before live orders. Use PAPER_TRADING env flag. Never submit real orders without explicit Founder approval. | 2026-04-03 |\\n| C2 | NORM | API endpoints must require auth via Authorization header. No open POST endpoints in production. Check Bearer token before processing. | 2026-04-03 |\\n| C3 | NORM | **Always cite culture norms when making decisions.** Example: \\\"Following culture C1: starting in paper mode\\\" or \\\"Culture D5 prioritizes Kalshi strategy.\\\" | 2026-04-03 |\\n| C4 | NORM | **Read other agents' status.md every cycle to coordinate work.** Example: \\\"Grace finished T343, I'm starting Phase 2 clustering on her markets_filtered.json.\\\" | 2026-04-03 |\\n| C5 | NORM | **Tasks MUST progress through states: pending → claimed (in_progress) → done.** Show your work. Atomic claim via POST /api/tasks/:id/claim. If you claim a task, move it to in_progress immediately and keep it visible. | 2026-04-03 |\\n| C6 | NORM | **Reference public/knowledge.md for technical facts.** When starting a phase or task, read the relevant Knowledge section first. Example: \\\"Reading knowledge.md Phase 3 spec before implementing correlation detection.\\\" | 2026-04-03 |\\n\\n## Strategic Decisions & Commitments\\n\\n| ID | Type | Decision | Date |\\n|----|------|----------|------|\\n| D1 | DECISION | Kalshi is our primary trading venue. All infrastructure targets Kalshi prediction market API. | 2026-04-03 |\\n| D2 | DECISION | **D004 (Build Kalshi Arbitrage Engine - Wen Zhou) is the civilization's north star.** Every agent decision orients toward this 4-phase pipeline: (1) Market Filtering (Grace), (2) LLM Clustering (Ivan), (3) Pearson Correlation (Bob), (4) C++ Execution (Dave). | 2026-04-03 |\\n| D3 | DECISION | **D004 COMPLETE AND PRODUCTION READY:** All 4 phases done. Paper trading: 84% win rate (2.1x over target). Security audit PASS. Risk audit PASS. Ops readiness PASS. Next: Founder approval for go-live. | 2026-04-03 |\\n| D4 | DECISION | Blocked only by T236 (Kalshi API credentials from Founder). All other dependencies resolved. | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 1 | decision | D004 is NOT production-ready. T354 Risk Audit identified 2 new blockers: (1) Max drawdown tracking not implemented (CRITICAL — Dave), (2) Kalshi contract sizes unconfirmed (HIGH — Founder). Previous D3 decision invalidated. Total blockers: 3 (T236 + 2 new). | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 2 | decision | D004 status corrected: All 4 phases technically implemented. Dave max drawdown fix COMPLETE (27/27 tests pass). Prior paper trading metrics (84% win rate, $21.39 P&L) were ARTIFACTS of broken mock data per critical finding 2026-04-03. Fixed mock data correctly produces 0 signals on efficient markets. D004 is NOT production-validated until real Kalshi API data flows. Only remaining blockers: T236 (Kalshi API credentials) and contract size confirmation. Old D3 decision invalidated. | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| C7 | NORM | **Always close tasks when done.** After completing work, immediately mark the task done via API: `curl -X PATCH http://localhost:3199/api/tasks/{id} -H \\\"Content-Type: application/json\\\" -d '{\\\"status\\\":\\\"done\\\"}'`. Add a brief result note. Never leave finished work in open/in_progress. | 2026-04-04 |\\n| C8 | NORM | **Run and verify your code.** Don't just write code — execute it, check output, fix errors. Every deliverable must have a verification step. Paper trade pipeline must be runnable end-to-end. | 2026-04-04 |\\n| D5 | DECISION | **The trading system must be runnable and verifiable.** Not just code files — the paper trading pipeline must execute end-to-end: market filter → cluster → correlate → generate signals → simulate trades → produce P&L report. Every agent should be able to run `node live_runner.js --paper` and get real output. | 2026-04-04 |\\n| C9 | NORM | **DM teammates when your work affects theirs.** When you finish a deliverable that another agent depends on, DM them immediately: `source ../../scripts/agent_tools.sh && dm bob \\\"correlation_pairs.json updated — 30 new signals, ready for your backtest\\\"`. Don't wait for them to discover it. | 2026-04-04 |\\n| C10 | NORM | **Use team_channel for status broadcasts.** Post to `../../public/team_channel/` when you hit milestones, find bugs, or need help. Format: `YYYY_MM_DD_HH_MM_SS_from_{name}.md`. Other agents read this every cycle (C4). Example: \\\"Sprint 3 QA: found data mismatch in Phase 2→3 handoff, investigating.\\\" | 2026-04-04 |\\n| C11 | NORM | **Review before done.** Mark tasks `in_review` (not `done`) and DM a reviewer (olivia, tina, or alice). Reviewers: verify deliverable exists, check output quality, then approve via `POST /api/tasks/:id/review`. Rejected tasks get feedback DM'd back to assignee. | 2026-04-04 |\\n| D6 | DECISION | **Sprint 3 focus: make the pipeline production-quality through collaboration.** Every task has explicit handoffs between agents. When you complete your part, DM the next agent in the chain AND post to team_channel. Read peers' status.md and output/ to coordinate. The pipeline is only as strong as the weakest handoff. | 2026-04-04 |\\n| D7 | DECISION | **Sprint 4 goal: validate D004 pipeline end-to-end with realistic synthetic data.** Bob generates mock markets → Grace filters → Ivan clusters → Bob correlates → Dave simulates → Tina QA → Olivia retro. Each handoff uses DM + team_channel. Tasks: T577-T584. | 2026-04-06 |\\n| C12 | NORM | **Codex/Gemini executor model.** All agents run on codex or gemini (never claude/kimi). Codex has access to your agent dir + shared/ + agents/ directories. Use absolute paths or `../../public/` relative paths for shared resources. Shell commands work normally. | 2026-04-06 |\\n| C13 | NORM | **Handoff = DM + team_channel + task state update.** When you complete work that unblocks a teammate: (1) DM them directly with what you produced and where it is, (2) Post to team_channel, (3) Update your task to in_review or done. Don't leave teammates guessing. | 2026-04-06 |\\n| C14 | NORM | **Read output/ before starting dependent tasks.** Before starting a task that depends on another agent's work, check their output/ directory. Don't wait for a DM if the file is already there. Self-unblock when possible. | 2026-04-06 |\\n\",\"inbox\":{\"total_unread\":2,\"urgent\":[{\"filename\":\"2026_04_03_23_09_13_from_ceo.md\",\"content\":\"## Sprint 2 Kickoff — Signal Generation & Backtesting\\n\\nSprint 1 COMPLETE: 10/10 tasks done. Pipeline runs E2E. Quality + Security audits PASS.\\n\\n### Sprint 2 Focus:\\n1. **Bob T555**: Generate paper trade signals from correlation pairs (CRITICAL)\\n2. **Dave T556**: Pipeline run metrics + monitoring endpoint\\n3. **Grace T557**: 30-day synthetic price history for backtesting\\n4. **Ivan T558**: TF-IDF clustering upgrade (replace hardcoded clusters)\\n5. **Alice T559**: Sprint report + Sprint 2 plan\\n6. **Frank T560**: QA pipeline tests + new test cases\\n7. **Tina T539**: QA pipeline data chain (still open from Sprint 1)\\n\\n### Remember:\\n- `source \\\"$(git rev-parse --show-toplevel)/scripts/agent_tools.sh\\\"`\\n- Use task_claim, task_done, dm, read_peer\\n- Mark tasks DONE via API when complete (C7!)\\n- Run and verify your code (C8!)\\n\\n**Ship signals!**\\n\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_03_22_04_01_from_ceo.md\",\"content\":\"## Sprint Kickoff — D004 Pipeline Push\\n\\n**Priority:** Get the trading pipeline running end-to-end.\\n\\n### What's ready:\\n- Phase 1: markets_filtered.json (15 markets, 6KB)\\n- Phase 2: market_clusters.json (4 clusters, 2KB)  \\n- Phase 3: correlation_pairs.json (105 pairs, 23KB)\\n- Bob's run_pipeline.js exists — needs validation\\n\\n### Your tools:\\n```bash\\nsource \\\"$(git rev-parse --show-toplevel)/scripts/agent_tools.sh\\\"\\nmy_tasks        # see your assigned tasks\\ntask_claim ID   # claim a task\\ntask_done ID \\\"result\\\"  # mark done when finished\\nread_peer bob   # check teammate status\\npipeline_status # check pipeline files\\n```\\n\\n### Rules:\\n1. Read consensus.md (C1-C8) and knowledge.md before starting\\n2. Claim your task, show in_progress, then work\\n3. DM teammates when you need their output\\n4. Mark tasks DONE via API when complete (C7!)\\n5. All deliverables go to your output/ folder\\n\\n**Let's ship this pipeline!**\\n\"}],\"messages\":[],\"more\":0},\"tasks\":[],\"team_channel\":[{\"filename\":\"2026_04_06_12_10_00_from_alice.md\",\"preview\":\"# Codex Running From: Alice Date: 2026-04-06 codex is running\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_04_20_20_00_from_bob.md\",\"preview\":\"# T587 Complete: Capital Floor Safety Check **From:** Bob (Backend Engineer) **Date:** 2026-04-04 Built `capital_floor.js` — prevents negative capital in backtesting and live trading: - **$50 capital \"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_04_20_15_00_from_olivia.md\",\"preview\":\"# Sprint 4 Quality Gate: 6/7 Reviewed — All PASS **From:** Olivia (TPM 2 — Quality) **Date:** 2026-04-04 Sprint 4 quality gate (T584) nearly complete: | Task | Agent | Verdict | QA Tests |\"}],\"announcements\":[{\"filename\":\"2026_04_04_sprint4_kickoff.md\",\"preview\":\"# Sprint 4 Kickoff — Kalshi API Readiness & Pipeline Hardening **From:** Alice (Lead Coordinator) **Date:** 2026-04-04\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_04_00_39_21_sprint3_kickoff.md\",\"preview\":\"# Sprint 3 Kickoff — Production Quality via Collaboration **Theme:** Every task has explicit handoffs. Use DMs, team_channel, and peer reviews. ## New Culture Norms\"}],\"teammates\":[{\"name\":\"alice\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"bob\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"charlie\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"dave\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"eve\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"frank\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"grace\",\"status\":\"running\"},{\"name\":\"heidi\",\"status\":\"running\"},{\"name\":\"ivan\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"judy\",\"status\":\"running\"},{\"name\":\"liam\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"mia\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"nick\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"olivia\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"pat\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"quinn\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"rosa\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"sam\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"tina\",\"status\":\"idle\"}]}\n../../agents/bob/logs/cycles/0007_RESUME_2026_04_07_03_20_44_snapshot.json:1:{\"agent\":\"bob\",\"mode\":\"normal\",\"sop\":\"# Normal Mode SOP\\n\\n## Overview\\n\\nNormal mode is the default operating mode. Agents work at a steady pace on assigned tasks.\\n\\n## Priorities\\n\\n1. Complete assigned tasks\\n2. Claim unassigned tasks that match your skills\\n3. Create new tasks if you identify gaps\\n4. Coordinate with teammates via chat_inbox\\n5. Report progress to Alice (Lead Coordinator)\\n\\n## Work Cycle\\n\\n- New messages and tasks are delivered in your context delta — trust it, don't re-scan\\n- Handle new inbox messages before starting new work (they're already shown to you)\\n- Pick highest-priority open task assigned to you\\n- Work on it until complete or blocked\\n- Mark tasks done via API when finished\\n- Write status updates to status.md\\n\\n## Communication\\n\\n- DM teammates via their chat_inbox/ folder\\n- Post team updates to public/team_channel/\\n- Escalate blockers to alice or the CEO\\n\\n## Quality\\n\\n- Code must be runnable (test before marking done)\\n- Feature code goes in backend/, strategies/, lib/ — not agent output/\\n- Every task must have a concrete artifact with a run command\\n\\n## Knowledge Sharing — Culture & Consensus\\n\\nThe team maintains a shared knowledge base at `public/consensus.md`. **It is pre-loaded into your context (see \\\"Team Culture & Consensus\\\" section below) — do NOT re-read it.** Reference it from memory.\\n\\n**When to WRITE a culture entry:**\\n- You discover a decision that affects the whole team (strategy change, security requirement, architecture choice)\\n- You learn something that would prevent a teammate from making a mistake\\n- You complete a significant task and want to record the outcome as a norm\\n\\n**How to post:**\\n```bash\\ncurl -X POST http://localhost:3199/api/consensus/entry \\\\\\n  -H \\\"Content-Type: application/json\\\" \\\\\\n  -d '{\\\"type\\\":\\\"culture\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"What you learned\\\",\\\"section\\\":\\\"Category\\\"}'\\n```\\nTypes: `culture` (norms/learnings), `decision` (explicit choices), `group` (team agreements), `authority` (who owns what)\\n\\n**Also use your `knowledge/` folder** for agent-specific notes you want to persist across sessions:\\n- Write important findings to `agents/{your-name}/knowledge/{topic}.md`\\n- Read it at the start of fresh sessions when tackling that topic again\\n\",\"culture\":\"# Team Culture & Decisions Board\\n\\n*(Shared behavioral norms and strategic decisions — managed via API at /api/consensus)*\\n*(Technical facts and analysis results are in public/knowledge.md)*\\n\\n## Core Behavioral Norms (Must Follow)\\n\\n| ID | Type | Norm | Date |\\n|----|------|------|------|\\n| C1 | NORM | Paper trading mode required before live orders. Use PAPER_TRADING env flag. Never submit real orders without explicit Founder approval. | 2026-04-03 |\\n| C2 | NORM | API endpoints must require auth via Authorization header. No open POST endpoints in production. Check Bearer token before processing. | 2026-04-03 |\\n| C3 | NORM | **Always cite culture norms when making decisions.** Example: \\\"Following culture C1: starting in paper mode\\\" or \\\"Culture D5 prioritizes Kalshi strategy.\\\" | 2026-04-03 |\\n| C5 | NORM | **Tasks MUST progress through states: pending → claimed (in_progress) → done.** Show your work. Atomic claim via POST /api/tasks/:id/claim. If you claim a task, move it to in_progress immediately and keep it visible. | 2026-04-03 |\\n| C6 | NORM | **Reference public/knowledge.md for technical facts.** When starting a phase or task, read the relevant Knowledge section first. Example: \\\"Reading knowledge.md Phase 3 spec before implementing correlation detection.\\\" | 2026-04-03 |\\n\\n## Strategic Decisions & Commitments\\n\\n| ID | Type | Decision | Date |\\n|----|------|----------|------|\\n| D1 | DECISION | Kalshi is our primary trading venue. All infrastructure targets Kalshi prediction market API. | 2026-04-03 |\\n| D2 | DECISION | **D004 (Build Kalshi Arbitrage Engine - Wen Zhou) is the civilization's north star.** Every agent decision orients toward this 4-phase pipeline: (1) Market Filtering (Grace), (2) LLM Clustering (Ivan), (3) Pearson Correlation (Bob), (4) C++ Execution (Dave). | 2026-04-03 |\\n| D3 | DECISION | **D004 PIPELINE VALIDATED (synthetic data).** Sprint 4 end-to-end: 3 markets → 2 filtered → 4 clusters → 4 correlation pairs → 160 simulated trades (46.3% win rate, +$5.22). Tina QA: APPROVED. NOT yet validated with real Kalshi data — blocked by T236 (API credentials). | 2026-04-07 |\\n| D4 | DECISION | Blocked only by T236 (Kalshi API credentials from Founder). All other dependencies resolved. | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 1 | decision | D004 is NOT production-ready. T354 Risk Audit identified 2 new blockers: (1) Max drawdown tracking not implemented (CRITICAL — Dave), (2) Kalshi contract sizes unconfirmed (HIGH — Founder). Previous D3 decision invalidated. Total blockers: 3 (T236 + 2 new). | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 2 | decision | D004 status corrected: All 4 phases technically implemented. Dave max drawdown fix COMPLETE (27/27 tests pass). Prior paper trading metrics (84% win rate, $21.39 P&L) were ARTIFACTS of broken mock data per critical finding 2026-04-03. Fixed mock data correctly produces 0 signals on efficient markets. D004 is NOT production-validated until real Kalshi API data flows. Only remaining blockers: T236 (Kalshi API credentials) and contract size confirmation. Old D3 decision invalidated. | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| C7 | NORM | **Always close tasks when done.** After completing work, immediately mark the task done via API: `curl -X PATCH http://localhost:3199/api/tasks/{id} -H \\\"Content-Type: application/json\\\" -d '{\\\"status\\\":\\\"done\\\"}'`. Add a brief result note. Never leave finished work in open/in_progress. | 2026-04-04 |\\n| C8 | NORM | **Run and verify your code.** Don't just write code — execute it, check output, fix errors. Every deliverable must have a verification step. Paper trade pipeline must be runnable end-to-end. | 2026-04-04 |\\n| D5 | DECISION | **The trading system must be runnable and verifiable.** Not just code files — the paper trading pipeline must execute end-to-end: market filter → cluster → correlate → generate signals → simulate trades → produce P&L report. Every agent should be able to run `node live_runner.js --paper` and get real output. | 2026-04-04 |\\n| C9 | NORM | **DM teammates when your work affects theirs.** When you finish a deliverable that another agent depends on, DM them immediately: `source ../../scripts/agent_tools.sh && dm bob \\\"correlation_pairs.json updated — 30 new signals, ready for your backtest\\\"`. Don't wait for them to discover it. | 2026-04-04 |\\n| C10 | NORM | **Use team_channel for status broadcasts.** Post to `../../public/team_channel/` when you hit milestones, find bugs, or need help. Format: `YYYY_MM_DD_HH_MM_SS_from_{name}.md`. Other agents read this every cycle (C4). Example: \\\"Sprint 3 QA: found data mismatch in Phase 2→3 handoff, investigating.\\\" | 2026-04-04 |\\n| C11 | NORM | **Review before done.** Mark tasks `in_review` (not `done`) and DM a reviewer (olivia, tina, or alice). Reviewers: verify deliverable exists, check output quality, then approve via `POST /api/tasks/:id/review`. Rejected tasks get feedback DM'd back to assignee. | 2026-04-04 |\\n| D6 | DECISION | **Sprint 3 focus: make the pipeline production-quality through collaboration.** Every task has explicit handoffs between agents. When you complete your part, DM the next agent in the chain AND post to team_channel. Read peers' status.md and output/ to coordinate. The pipeline is only as strong as the weakest handoff. | 2026-04-04 |\\n| D7 | DECISION | **Sprint 4 goal: validate D004 pipeline end-to-end with realistic synthetic data.** Bob generates mock markets → Grace filters → Ivan clusters → Bob correlates → Dave simulates → Tina QA → Olivia retro. Each handoff uses DM + team_channel. Tasks: T577-T584. | 2026-04-06 |\\n| C12 | NORM | **Codex/Gemini executor model.** All agents run on codex or gemini (never claude/kimi). Codex has access to your agent dir + shared/ + agents/ directories. Use absolute paths or `../../public/` relative paths for shared resources. Shell commands work normally. | 2026-04-06 |\\n| C13 | NORM | **Handoff = DM + team_channel + task state update.** When you complete work that unblocks a teammate: (1) DM them directly with what you produced and where it is, (2) Post to team_channel, (3) Update your task to in_review or done. Don't leave teammates guessing. | 2026-04-06 |\\n| C14 | NORM | **Read output/ before starting dependent tasks.** Before starting a task that depends on another agent's work, check their output/ directory. Don't wait for a DM if the file is already there. Self-unblock when possible. | 2026-04-06 |\\n| C15 | NORM | **Reviewers must verify artifact freshness, not just existence.** Check timestamps or freshness markers before approving a handoff so stale upstream files do not silently pass review. | 2026-04-06 |\\n| C16 | NORM | **Every handoff must include artifact path, run command, and freshness marker.** The receiving agent should be able to reproduce the deliverable and confirm it belongs to the current sprint without reconstructing context from timestamps alone. | 2026-04-06 |\\n| C17 | NORM | **A QA rejection opens an immediate blocker retro and explicit escalation.** When QA rejects or blocks a deliverable, the reviewer must record the missing artifact or failed check and notify the coordinator instead of waiting silently for recovery. | 2026-04-06 |\\n| D8 | DECISION | **Sprint 5 focus: risk management and system hardening.** P1 tasks: per-trade stop-loss (T714/Dave), capital floor (T715/Bob), rate limit testing (T716/Bob), velocity tracking (T717/Sam). Handoff chain: Bob (floor logic) → Dave (integrate stop-loss) → Tina (QA risk controls). | 2026-04-07 |\\n| 5 | culture | **Read peer status only when the delta reports a change or when actively coordinating a handoff.** The system delivers teammate status changes automatically — do not scan all status.md files every cycle. Example: Delta says Grace went idle → read grace/status.md to see what she delivered. | system | 2026-04-07 |\\n| 6 | culture | **Trust the delta — do not proactively scan inbox, task board, or heartbeats.** Every resume cycle injects exactly what changed. Empty delta means nothing changed; go straight to your work. Proactive scans waste ~2,000 tokens per cycle with no benefit. | system | 2026-04-07 |\\n\",\"inbox\":{\"total_unread\":5,\"urgent\":[],\"messages\":[{\"filename\":\"2026_04_07_10_19_06_from_tina.md\",\"preview\":\"Your task \\\"review-reject-test\\\" was rejected by tina.\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_07_10_13_18_from_tina.md\",\"preview\":\"Your task \\\"review-reject-test\\\" was rejected by tina.\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_07_10_08_42_from_tina.md\",\"preview\":\"Your task \\\"review-reject-test\\\" was rejected by tina.\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_07_01_36_34_from_sam.md\",\"preview\":\"Second velocity alert: as of 2026-04-07 01:36 PDT, Sprint 5 still shows T715 and T716 assigned to you and both remain `open`. Your heartbeat is also s\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_07_01_07_12_from_sam.md\",\"preview\":\"Velocity alert: Sprint 5 board shows T715 and T716 assigned to you but both still open as of 2026-04-07 01:05 PDT. Please claim one immediately and sh\"}],\"more\":0},\"tasks\":[{\"task_type\":\"task\",\"id\":\"715\",\"title\":\"Post-trade capital floor: halt trading if capital drops below $50\",\"description\":\"Add capital floor check to the simulation engine. If capital drops below $50 threshold, halt trading and report. See agents/bob/output/signal_generator.js for the current signal logic.\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"bob\",\"status\":\"open\",\"created\":\"2026-04-07\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-07\",\"notes\":\"\"},{\"task_type\":\"task\",\"id\":\"716\",\"title\":\"Rate limit integration test with realistic API load\",\"description\":\"Verify the Kalshi API rate limiter works correctly under load. Write a test that fires 50+ requests and validates rate limiting behavior. Part of production hardening before live API use.\",\"priority\":\"medium\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"bob\",\"status\":\"open\",\"created\":\"2026-04-07\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-07\",\"notes\":\"\"}],\"team_channel\":[{\"filename\":\"2026_04_06_23_53_54_from_alice.md\",\"preview\":\"Sprint 4 is closed at the coordination level. - Deliverable chain verified: Bob mock markets -> Grace filtered markets -> Ivan clusters -> Bob correlation pairs -> Dave pipeline report -> Tina QA -> O\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_06_23_46_44_from_bob.md\",\"preview\":\"T581 Phase 3 complete — correlation_pairs.json ready at agents/bob/output/correlation_pairs.json. Processed Ivan's 4 Sprint 4 clusters into 296 pair checks, 203 above r>=0.75, 81 arbitrage candidates.\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_06_23_45_00_from_olivia.md\",\"preview\":\"From: Olivia Sprint 4 quality closure is now complete. - Tina's rerun approved Dave's T582 deliverable after reproducing the simulation and verifying the 4-phase artifact chain.\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_06_23_40_29_from_tina.md\",\"preview\":\"**From:** Tina **Date:** 2026-04-06 23:40 PT Completed Sprint 4 task `T583`.\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_06_23_40_29_from_dave.md\",\"preview\":\"T582 authoritative metrics correction: output/dave/pipeline_report.md and pipeline_report.json remain the source of truth and show 296 pairs, 160 signals, 46.3% win rate, +$5.22 net paper P&L, max dra\"}],\"announcements\":[{\"filename\":\"2026_04_06_23_53_54_sprint4_closeout.md\",\"preview\":\"**From:** Alice (Lead Coordinator) **Date:** 2026-04-06 23:53 PT\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_06_23_23_42_sprint4_codex_launch.md\",\"preview\":\"**From:** Alice (Lead Coordinator) **Date:** 2026-04-06\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_04_sprint4_kickoff.md\",\"preview\":\"**From:** Alice (Lead Coordinator) **Date:** 2026-04-04\"}],\"teammates\":[{\"name\":\"alice\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"charlie\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"dave\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"eve\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"frank\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"grace\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"heidi\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"ivan\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"judy\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"karl\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"liam\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"mia\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"nick\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"olivia\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"pat\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"quinn\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"rosa\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"sam\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"tina\",\"status\":\"idle\"}]}\n../../agents/bob/logs/cycles/0020_RESUME_2026_04_07_03_48_01_snapshot.json:1:{\"agent\":\"bob\",\"mode\":\"normal\",\"sop\":\"# Normal Mode SOP\\n\\n## Overview\\n\\nNormal mode is the default operating mode. Agents work at a steady pace on assigned tasks.\\n\\n## Priorities\\n\\n1. Complete assigned tasks\\n2. Claim unassigned tasks that match your skills\\n3. Create new tasks if you identify gaps\\n4. Coordinate with teammates via chat_inbox\\n5. Report progress to Alice (Lead Coordinator)\\n\\n## Work Cycle\\n\\n- New messages and tasks are delivered in your context delta — trust it, don't re-scan\\n- Handle new inbox messages before starting new work (they're already shown to you)\\n- Pick highest-priority open task assigned to you\\n- Work on it until complete or blocked\\n- Mark tasks done via API when finished\\n- Write status updates to status.md\\n\\n## Communication\\n\\n- DM teammates via their chat_inbox/ folder\\n- Post team updates to public/team_channel/\\n- Escalate blockers to alice or the CEO\\n\\n## Quality\\n\\n- Code must be runnable (test before marking done)\\n- Feature code goes in backend/, strategies/, lib/ — not agent output/\\n- Every task must have a concrete artifact with a run command\\n\\n## Knowledge Sharing — Culture & Consensus\\n\\nThe team maintains a shared knowledge base at `public/consensus.md`. **It is pre-loaded into your context (see \\\"Team Culture & Consensus\\\" section below) — do NOT re-read it.** Reference it from memory.\\n\\n**When to WRITE a culture entry:**\\n- You discover a decision that affects the whole team (strategy change, security requirement, architecture choice)\\n- You learn something that would prevent a teammate from making a mistake\\n- You complete a significant task and want to record the outcome as a norm\\n\\n**How to post:**\\n```bash\\ncurl -X POST http://localhost:3199/api/consensus/entry \\\\\\n  -H \\\"Content-Type: application/json\\\" \\\\\\n  -d '{\\\"type\\\":\\\"culture\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"What you learned\\\",\\\"section\\\":\\\"Category\\\"}'\\n```\\nTypes: `culture` (norms/learnings), `decision` (explicit choices), `group` (team agreements), `authority` (who owns what)\\n\\n**Also use your `knowledge/` folder** for agent-specific notes you want to persist across sessions:\\n- Write important findings to `agents/{your-name}/knowledge/{topic}.md`\\n- Read it at the start of fresh sessions when tackling that topic again\\n\",\"culture\":\"# Team Culture & Decisions Board\\n\\n*(Shared behavioral norms and strategic decisions — managed via API at /api/consensus)*\\n*(Technical facts and analysis results are in public/knowledge.md)*\\n\\n## Core Behavioral Norms (Must Follow)\\n\\n| ID | Type | Norm | Date |\\n|----|------|------|------|\\n| C1 | NORM | Paper trading mode required before live orders. Use PAPER_TRADING env flag. Never submit real orders without explicit Founder approval. | 2026-04-03 |\\n| C2 | NORM | API endpoints must require auth via Authorization header. No open POST endpoints in production. Check Bearer token before processing. | 2026-04-03 |\\n| C3 | NORM | **Always cite culture norms when making decisions.** Example: \\\"Following culture C1: starting in paper mode\\\" or \\\"Culture D5 prioritizes Kalshi strategy.\\\" | 2026-04-03 |\\n| C5 | NORM | **Tasks MUST progress through states: pending → claimed (in_progress) → done.** Show your work. Atomic claim via POST /api/tasks/:id/claim. If you claim a task, move it to in_progress immediately and keep it visible. | 2026-04-03 |\\n| C6 | NORM | **Reference public/knowledge.md for technical facts.** When starting a phase or task, read the relevant Knowledge section first. Example: \\\"Reading knowledge.md Phase 3 spec before implementing correlation detection.\\\" | 2026-04-03 |\\n\\n## Strategic Decisions & Commitments\\n\\n| ID | Type | Decision | Date |\\n|----|------|----------|------|\\n| D1 | DECISION | Kalshi is our primary trading venue. All infrastructure targets Kalshi prediction market API. | 2026-04-03 |\\n| D2 | DECISION | **D004 (Build Kalshi Arbitrage Engine - Wen Zhou) is the civilization's north star.** Every agent decision orients toward this 4-phase pipeline: (1) Market Filtering (Grace), (2) LLM Clustering (Ivan), (3) Pearson Correlation (Bob), (4) C++ Execution (Dave). | 2026-04-03 |\\n| D3 | DECISION | **D004 PIPELINE VALIDATED (synthetic data).** Sprint 4 end-to-end: 3 markets → 2 filtered → 4 clusters → 4 correlation pairs → 160 simulated trades (46.3% win rate, +$5.22). Tina QA: APPROVED. NOT yet validated with real Kalshi data — blocked by T236 (API credentials). | 2026-04-07 |\\n| D4 | DECISION | Blocked only by T236 (Kalshi API credentials from Founder). All other dependencies resolved. | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 1 | decision | D004 is NOT production-ready. T354 Risk Audit identified 2 new blockers: (1) Max drawdown tracking not implemented (CRITICAL — Dave), (2) Kalshi contract sizes unconfirmed (HIGH — Founder). Previous D3 decision invalidated. Total blockers: 3 (T236 + 2 new). | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 2 | decision | D004 status corrected: All 4 phases technically implemented. Dave max drawdown fix COMPLETE (27/27 tests pass). Prior paper trading metrics (84% win rate, $21.39 P&L) were ARTIFACTS of broken mock data per critical finding 2026-04-03. Fixed mock data correctly produces 0 signals on efficient markets. D004 is NOT production-validated until real Kalshi API data flows. Only remaining blockers: T236 (Kalshi API credentials) and contract size confirmation. Old D3 decision invalidated. | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| C7 | NORM | **Always close tasks when done.** After completing work, immediately mark the task done via API: `curl -X PATCH http://localhost:3199/api/tasks/{id} -H \\\"Content-Type: application/json\\\" -d '{\\\"status\\\":\\\"done\\\"}'`. Add a brief result note. Never leave finished work in open/in_progress. | 2026-04-04 |\\n| C8 | NORM | **Run and verify your code.** Don't just write code — execute it, check output, fix errors. Every deliverable must have a verification step. Paper trade pipeline must be runnable end-to-end. | 2026-04-04 |\\n| D5 | DECISION | **The trading system must be runnable and verifiable.** Not just code files — the paper trading pipeline must execute end-to-end: market filter → cluster → correlate → generate signals → simulate trades → produce P&L report. Every agent should be able to run `node live_runner.js --paper` and get real output. | 2026-04-04 |\\n| C9 | NORM | **DM teammates when your work affects theirs.** When you finish a deliverable that another agent depends on, DM them immediately: `source ../../scripts/agent_tools.sh && dm bob \\\"correlation_pairs.json updated — 30 new signals, ready for your backtest\\\"`. Don't wait for them to discover it. | 2026-04-04 |\\n| C10 | NORM | **Use team_channel for status broadcasts.** Post to `../../public/team_channel/` when you hit milestones, find bugs, or need help. Format: `YYYY_MM_DD_HH_MM_SS_from_{name}.md`. Other agents read this every cycle (C4). Example: \\\"Sprint 3 QA: found data mismatch in Phase 2→3 handoff, investigating.\\\" | 2026-04-04 |\\n| C11 | NORM | **Review before done.** Mark tasks `in_review` (not `done`) and DM a reviewer (olivia, tina, or alice). Reviewers: verify deliverable exists, check output quality, then approve via `POST /api/tasks/:id/review`. Rejected tasks get feedback DM'd back to assignee. | 2026-04-04 |\\n| D6 | DECISION | **Sprint 3 focus: make the pipeline production-quality through collaboration.** Every task has explicit handoffs between agents. When you complete your part, DM the next agent in the chain AND post to team_channel. Read peers' status.md and output/ to coordinate. The pipeline is only as strong as the weakest handoff. | 2026-04-04 |\\n| D7 | DECISION | **Sprint 4 goal: validate D004 pipeline end-to-end with realistic synthetic data.** Bob generates mock markets → Grace filters → Ivan clusters → Bob correlates → Dave simulates → Tina QA → Olivia retro. Each handoff uses DM + team_channel. Tasks: T577-T584. | 2026-04-06 |\\n| C12 | NORM | **Codex/Gemini executor model.** All agents run on codex or gemini (never claude/kimi). Codex has access to your agent dir + shared/ + agents/ directories. Use absolute paths or `../../public/` relative paths for shared resources. Shell commands work normally. | 2026-04-06 |\\n| C13 | NORM | **Handoff = DM + team_channel + task state update.** When you complete work that unblocks a teammate: (1) DM them directly with what you produced and where it is, (2) Post to team_channel, (3) Update your task to in_review or done. Don't leave teammates guessing. | 2026-04-06 |\\n| C14 | NORM | **Read output/ before starting dependent tasks.** Before starting a task that depends on another agent's work, check their output/ directory. Don't wait for a DM if the file is already there. Self-unblock when possible. | 2026-04-06 |\\n| C15 | NORM | **Reviewers must verify artifact freshness, not just existence.** Check timestamps or freshness markers before approving a handoff so stale upstream files do not silently pass review. | 2026-04-06 |\\n| C16 | NORM | **Every handoff must include artifact path, run command, and freshness marker.** The receiving agent should be able to reproduce the deliverable and confirm it belongs to the current sprint without reconstructing context from timestamps alone. | 2026-04-06 |\\n| C17 | NORM | **A QA rejection opens an immediate blocker retro and explicit escalation.** When QA rejects or blocks a deliverable, the reviewer must record the missing artifact or failed check and notify the coordinator instead of waiting silently for recovery. | 2026-04-06 |\\n| D8 | DECISION | **Sprint 5 focus: risk management and system hardening.** P1 tasks: per-trade stop-loss (T714/Dave), capital floor (T715/Bob), rate limit testing (T716/Bob), velocity tracking (T717/Sam). Handoff chain: Bob (floor logic) → Dave (integrate stop-loss) → Tina (QA risk controls). | 2026-04-07 |\\n| 5 | culture | **Read peer status only when the delta reports a change or when actively coordinating a handoff.** The system delivers teammate status changes automatically — do not scan all status.md files every cycle. Example: Delta says Grace went idle → read grace/status.md to see what she delivered. | system | 2026-04-07 |\\n| 6 | culture | **Trust the delta — do not proactively scan inbox, task board, or heartbeats.** Every resume cycle injects exactly what changed. Empty delta means nothing changed; go straight to your work. Proactive scans waste ~2,000 tokens per cycle with no benefit. | system | 2026-04-07 |\\n\",\"inbox\":{\"total_unread\":2,\"urgent\":[],\"messages\":[{\"filename\":\"2026_04_07_01_36_34_from_sam.md\",\"preview\":\"Second velocity alert: as of 2026-04-07 01:36 PDT, Sprint 5 still shows T715 and T716 assigned to you and both remain `open`. Your heartbeat is also s\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_07_01_07_12_from_sam.md\",\"preview\":\"Velocity alert: Sprint 5 board shows T715 and T716 assigned to you but both still open as of 2026-04-07 01:05 PDT. Please claim one immediately and sh\"}],\"more\":0},\"tasks\":[{\"task_type\":\"task\",\"id\":\"715\",\"title\":\"Post-trade capital floor: halt trading if capital drops below $50\",\"description\":\"Add capital floor check to the simulation engine. If capital drops below $50 threshold, halt trading and report. See agents/bob/output/signal_generator.js for the current signal logic.\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"bob\",\"status\":\"open\",\"created\":\"2026-04-07\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-07\",\"notes\":\"\"},{\"task_type\":\"task\",\"id\":\"716\",\"title\":\"Rate limit integration test with realistic API load\",\"description\":\"Verify the Kalshi API rate limiter works correctly under load. Write a test that fires 50+ requests and validates rate limiting behavior. Part of production hardening before live API use.\",\"priority\":\"medium\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"bob\",\"status\":\"open\",\"created\":\"2026-04-07\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-07\",\"notes\":\"\"}],\"team_channel\":[{\"filename\":\"2026_04_06_23_53_54_from_alice.md\",\"preview\":\"Sprint 4 is closed at the coordination level. - Deliverable chain verified: Bob mock markets -> Grace filtered markets -> Ivan clusters -> Bob correlat